        <div class="key-takeaway"><strong>Key takeaway:</strong> For streaming, a VPN is about the right region + stable playback, and staying leak-safe (DNS/IPv6/WebRTC).</div>

        <div class="note">
          <strong>Related:</strong> <a href="/en-us/blog/proxy-vs-vpn.html">Proxy vs VPN</a>
        </div>

        <h2>When VPN protection works (and when it doesn’t)</h2>
        <p>
          VPNs are strong at protecting traffic in transit and hiding your public IP from sites — but they don’t automatically stop
          <strong>cookies</strong>, <strong>account logins</strong>, or <strong>fingerprinting</strong>. For streaming accounts, remember:
          if you’re logged in, the platform still knows it’s you — the VPN mainly changes network signals (IP/region) and improves privacy on the path.
        </p>

