          <h3 style="margin:0 0 10px; color:#000; font-weight:800;">Diagram: Why “closer server” usually streams better</h3>
          <p style="margin:0 0 12px; color:#000; font-weight:800;">
            Distance increases latency. Latency isn’t the same as bandwidth, but it affects buffering and startup time.
          </p>
          <div style="overflow-x:auto;">
            <svg width="980" height="250" viewBox="0 0 980 250" role="img" aria-label="Bar chart comparing latency by server distance" style="max-width:100%; height:auto; color:#000;">
